00:14:05.150 --> 00:14:06.230
in the digital era.

00:14:06.230 --> 00:14:08.030
How do we get beyond
the distractions

00:14:08.030 --> 00:14:10.940
so that we can focus in on
what is really happening

00:14:10.940 --> 00:14:12.590
and the bigger picture?

00:14:12.590 --> 00:14:16.100
Or to put it in another
way, one of the statistics

00:14:16.100 --> 00:14:17.600
that I came across
in my research

00:14:17.600 --> 00:14:21.860
was that the average text
message takes about 2.2 seconds

00:14:21.860 --> 00:14:23.620
to come into your phone.

00:14:23.620 --> 00:14:26.570
And that 2.2 seconds,
what we see happen

00:14:26.570 --> 00:14:29.720
is that the error
rates get doubled.

00:14:29.720 --> 00:14:31.880
2.2 seconds, you
double your error rate

00:14:31.880 --> 00:14:33.890
on simple tasks like adding.

00:14:33.890 --> 00:14:35.900
If you have a text
message that you send,

00:14:35.900 --> 00:14:38.270
which takes an average
of 3.3 seconds,

00:14:38.270 --> 00:14:40.400
it triples your error rates.

00:14:40.400 --> 00:14:43.430
Now imagine the impact of
that on your productivity.

00:14:43.430 --> 00:14:46.400
Get this, beyond that, every
time you get distracted

00:14:46.400 --> 00:14:49.370
by your phone it takes
approximately 11 minutes

00:14:49.370 --> 00:14:52.650
to return to the focus on the
task you were doing before.

00:14:52.650 --> 00:14:55.790
So that text message that's now
doubled your error messages,

00:14:55.790 --> 00:14:58.370
has now stolen 11 minutes
of your productivity

00:14:58.370 --> 00:15:01.550
that you could have been doing
other things with in your life.

00:15:01.550 --> 00:15:04.160
So how do we get over that?

00:15:04.160 --> 00:15:07.160
A lot of people immediately
turn to a digital detox.

00:15:07.160 --> 00:15:09.620
I feel so saturated with
technology in my life,

00:15:09.620 --> 00:15:12.650
I just need to get away from
it all for a little bit.

00:15:12.650 --> 00:15:14.360
Now, that strategy
is very effective

00:15:14.360 --> 00:15:16.100
if you want to simply detox.

00:15:16.100 --> 00:15:19.010
But what we found is
that just like in diets,

00:15:19.010 --> 00:15:22.880
short term diets ultimately fail
because they're only short term

00:15:22.880 --> 00:15:23.910
interventions.

00:15:23.910 --> 00:15:26.840
And I think what we need to do
is be able to create patterns

00:15:26.840 --> 00:15:29.420
in our life for dealing
with technology in a way

00:15:29.420 --> 00:15:33.210
that we can live alongside it,
that not only makes us happier

00:15:33.210 --> 00:15:35.720
while we're in the process,
but will make us happier

00:15:35.720 --> 00:15:37.550
for the long run as well.

00:15:37.550 --> 00:15:40.190
Because just like the cavemen
who discovered fire back

00:15:40.190 --> 00:15:43.100
in the day, right, they
knew it was dangerous.

00:15:43.100 --> 00:15:45.860
But nobody once suggested,
let's get rid of fire.

00:15:45.860 --> 00:15:47.420
I think fire is a
really bad idea.

00:15:47.420 --> 00:15:49.550
It burned me the last
time I touched it.

00:15:49.550 --> 00:15:52.340
No, you simply learn how to
use the tool better so that you

00:15:52.340 --> 00:15:55.190
can then be able to take
advantage of the power that

00:15:55.190 --> 00:15:56.150
comes with it.

00:15:56.150 --> 00:15:57.980
And that's my approach
to technology.

00:15:57.980 --> 00:16:00.530
If we're able to begin to
use this tool for its best

00:16:00.530 --> 00:16:02.540
and highest purposes,
then we'll be

00:16:02.540 --> 00:16:04.910
able to capture the
power for ourselves

00:16:04.910 --> 00:16:07.220
as opposed to getting burned.

00:16:07.220 --> 00:16:09.200
So the key here, we've
got to figure out

00:16:09.200 --> 00:16:12.330
how do we stop using
technology to zone out,

00:16:12.330 --> 00:16:14.600
and how do we use it to
start tuning in on our life?

00:16:14.600 --> 00:16:16.058
Because I really
sense that there's

00:16:16.058 --> 00:16:17.750
this bifurcation
[? that it has ?]

00:16:17.750 --> 00:16:20.250
that technology is
either one or the other.

00:16:20.250 --> 00:16:21.590
There's no middle ground here.

00:16:21.590 --> 00:16:23.300
Either it's causing
us to move away

00:16:23.300 --> 00:16:25.010
from our goals and
our priorities,

00:16:25.010 --> 00:16:27.530
or it's helping us
move closer to them.

00:16:27.530 --> 00:16:30.200
And so I have five strategies I
want to share with you briefly

00:16:30.200 --> 00:16:30.700
today.

00:16:30.700 --> 00:16:33.380
But I'll give you some takeaways
that you can just immediately

00:16:33.380 --> 00:16:36.200
put into action in your own
life that are very simple,

00:16:36.200 --> 00:16:38.360
but I think are very
eye opening as well.

00:16:38.360 --> 00:16:40.670
And the first one is
to know your stats.

00:16:40.670 --> 00:16:43.580
Now the average smartphone
user checks their phone

00:16:43.580 --> 00:16:46.250
150 times a day.

00:16:46.250 --> 00:16:48.930
Now you may think, well,
I don't check my phone

00:16:48.930 --> 00:16:49.820
100-- there's no way.

00:16:49.820 --> 00:16:52.010
That's crazy talk.

00:16:52.010 --> 00:16:53.100
Maybe not.

00:16:53.100 --> 00:16:55.070
But if you did, the
average smartphone user,

00:16:55.070 --> 00:16:57.500
if it took them one minute
to pick up their phone,

00:16:57.500 --> 00:16:59.794
check the message and
put it back down--

00:16:59.794 --> 00:17:01.460
that's ignoring the
11 minutes of trying

00:17:01.460 --> 00:17:03.860
to get back to the task
before that-- so just assume

00:17:03.860 --> 00:17:04.819
one minute.

00:17:04.819 --> 00:17:08.270
That would be the equivalent
of 2 and 1/2 hours of your day

00:17:08.270 --> 00:17:10.410
just picking up your phone.

00:17:10.410 --> 00:17:12.349
Which is crazy-- if
you multiply that

00:17:12.349 --> 00:17:13.930
by the 12 months
of the year, that's

00:17:13.930 --> 00:17:18.079
38 days a year of your life that
you're picking up your phone,

00:17:18.079 --> 00:17:20.630
not even doing anything,
just picking it up.

00:17:20.630 --> 00:17:23.000
If you don't believe
me, I have a great app

00:17:23.000 --> 00:17:24.319
