00:18:25.770 --> 00:18:29.190
But what I think is
interesting is that at no point

00:18:29.190 --> 00:18:32.010
did I actually dip
below the 2 and 1/2

00:18:32.010 --> 00:18:34.860
hours of pickups that were
the average smart phone

00:18:34.860 --> 00:18:35.970
user for the day.

00:18:35.970 --> 00:18:39.270
My lowest amount of time is
two hours and 37 minutes.

00:18:39.270 --> 00:18:41.610
So this was a really good
litmus check for me, to say,

00:18:41.610 --> 00:18:44.700
OK, you know, I thought
I was behaving one way.

00:18:44.700 --> 00:18:47.472
Now I know for a fact
how I'm behaving,

00:18:47.472 --> 00:18:48.930
and I don't want
to live like this.

00:18:48.930 --> 00:18:51.650
This is not who I want to be
and how I want to spend my time.

00:18:51.650 --> 00:18:54.160
I actually have a lot of other
things I want to be doing.

00:18:54.160 --> 00:18:55.402
And if you're like me--

00:18:55.402 --> 00:18:56.610
I have some great strategies.

00:18:56.610 --> 00:18:58.080
My colleague Alexa
and I are going

00:18:58.080 --> 00:18:59.860
to be doing a workshop
right after this

00:18:59.860 --> 00:19:02.640
to talk about digital
time management

00:19:02.640 --> 00:19:05.850
and how we can rethink and
reshape some of our behavior

00:19:05.850 --> 00:19:08.190
patterns to recapture
that time in our lives

00:19:08.190 --> 00:19:11.320
and what that looks like
on a very practical level.

00:19:11.320 --> 00:19:12.702
But that's the first step.

00:19:12.702 --> 00:19:14.160
You've got to know
where you're at.

00:19:14.160 --> 00:19:15.576
You've got to get
real, and you've

00:19:15.576 --> 00:19:18.480
got to create a baseline so
you know where your behavior is

00:19:18.480 --> 00:19:21.390
and where you stack up
with where you want to be.

00:19:21.390 --> 00:19:24.450
The second step is to tap
into your third prong.

00:19:24.450 --> 00:19:26.940
Now, the third prong, just
like an electrical outlet

00:19:26.940 --> 00:19:28.740
has usually two prongs on it.

00:19:28.740 --> 00:19:31.020
If you add a third
prong to the cord,

00:19:31.020 --> 00:19:32.910
you get a grounding
wire that begins

00:19:32.910 --> 00:19:34.740
to channel and focus energy.

00:19:34.740 --> 00:19:37.620
And so I call this grounding
wire your third prong,

00:19:37.620 --> 00:19:40.140
to help you think about
what it is in your life that

00:19:40.140 --> 00:19:42.840
are your set of guiding
principles and beliefs that

00:19:42.840 --> 00:19:45.330
shape the way you think
about your technology use.

00:19:45.330 --> 00:19:48.594
It may be something that you've
never even contemplated before.

00:19:48.594 --> 00:19:50.760
If you're a parent, you've
probably thought about it

00:19:50.760 --> 00:19:53.051
in terms of your children,
how you want your kids to be

00:19:53.051 --> 00:19:54.876
spending time with technology.

00:19:54.876 --> 00:19:56.250
But it took me
some time to think

00:19:56.250 --> 00:19:59.890
through what does that mean for
me and what I want to be doing.

00:19:59.890 --> 00:20:02.430
And one of the things that I
came across with me for myself

00:20:02.430 --> 00:20:03.870
was that I'm at a
place in my life

00:20:03.870 --> 00:20:05.760
where I really
want to be growing.

00:20:05.760 --> 00:20:07.140
I want to be
learning, and I want

00:20:07.140 --> 00:20:09.100
to invest a lot in my family.

00:20:09.100 --> 00:20:11.430
And so my set of
principles and intentions

00:20:11.430 --> 00:20:15.630
all began to gather around
that set of intentions,

00:20:15.630 --> 00:20:17.790
that third prong that
shaped the rest of what

00:20:17.790 --> 00:20:19.630
I'm about to tell you.

00:20:19.630 --> 00:20:22.470
So some people who want
to set their intentions

00:20:22.470 --> 00:20:24.720
